76561198066757242,Recommended,293780,23766553,"Posted: 24 June, 2016",all,Spoo,"CrawlThis game is a refreshing entrant into the couch-multiplayer games genre.As much as these types of games are appreciated within the gaming community, Crawl offers something more unique that I personally had never seen before in a dungeon crawler. That is saying a lot, given how many of those types of games are on Steam alone.Unlike many of those games, Crawl is played out in a king of the hill style, with one player controlling the hero, and the other three controlling monsters and traps. Kill the hero: become him. This is a mechanic I had never seen before and am thouroughly impressed with how well it was implemented. It draws you in. The fights and tension between players is genuine, and when you find yourself shouting with excitement... or resentment, without even realizing it, that is a very good thing.The art is amazing. As someone who appreciates pixel art style, especially the retro, arcade-type pixelation, the art and animation immediately stood out to me. Very fluid and well done but at the same time still able to hold that nostalgic factor.The soundtrack, while limited, shines where it is implemented. A very omnious feeling throughout, and the tracks change appropriately depending on certain events such as a player approaching victory or entering a boss fight.The gameplay is well balanced and thought out, characters and monsters can be upgraded, and the rubber-banding is appropriate. Players can come back from any defecit at any point in the game.Overall OpinionThe game is a must buy in my opinion. It is best played with friends, but I have enjoyed several hours of playtime with the AI, which can give you a run for your money. Updates are still on the horizon at the time of this review, showing the devs really care about this game and its success. Their forum on their website posts upcoming updates for the game and gives players the oppurtunity to give feedback, which is a welcome stand-out from a lot of other developers.With more content on the horizon, Crawl is shaping up to be a very promising game. As of now even, it is definitely a complete, polished game worthy of many hours of playtime."
,Recommended,293780,11578002,"Posted: 6 August, 2014",all,Baron Unread [F] for HL3,"Ok, so I've never done any review. Ever.But this game deserves it. So let's get started.First of all, what is Crawl?Like the name suggests, along with the pictures, you might understand that it's your usual dungeon crawler. But it isn't.It IS a dungeon crawler. But not in the likes of Diablo or Torchlight. It's more of a skilled-hack 'n' slash-dungeon crawler.And TBH, as a fan of dungeon crawlers, this is the best one I've ever seen.I might also add that I may have a little bias about it because of the god damned amazing music/teaser trailer. But I digress.As I've said before, it's not your usual dungeon crawler. And there's also another reason because of that. It's not open world and it's not story driven. It's an arcade game.And it does it really well. The game, as you may already know if you're reading this review because you want to be sure that the game is nice, is a local co-op/versus game.""But Baron! I don't have any friends! I'm a god damned loner!""Well they added some bots which you can play against for ""practice while you're waiting for your friends"". And they're also going to add multiplayer in the near future. So that's good. Because I'm also a loner.How's the gameplay?It's good, 10/potato.Just kidding. The gameplay is absolutely amazing, but to be played at its best you NEED a controller. Which isn't a problem FOR ME, but might me a problem for the people who can't afford to buy one. Any controller that is supported by steam will do. But personally I prefer to use a PS3 controller with the scarlet crush drivers.As I've said at the start of this review, the game is part hack 'n' slash. And it's a blast. The controls are responsive and easy to learn. It's literally just two buttons. I've never found myself saying ""God damn it, I didn't want to do that!"", if I died it was 90% of the times because of the skill of the bots or because I wasn't good enough.The only problem about it might be that they made the button to attack also the button to ""use"" stuff. I've found myself sometimes entering the final boss battle by mistake with little health remaining and dying by the hands of the bots controlling the boss.How are the graphics?Well, I really don't know, I don't have eyes to see a god damned PICTURE ON THE STORE PAGE.TL;DR?Do you like co-op fast paced hack 'n' slash dungeon crawlers games? Then this is for you, I guess, I've never heard of games like this, but whatever, everyone has their own fetish.Gib scor plzKK bb, from a scale from 1 to 10:Music: 10Gameplay: 10 [seeing yourself getting♥♥♥♥♥♥♥to death just to kill the same bot that killed you is an amazing feeling]Graphics: 10Overall: 10On a side note, it runs on my toaster, 10/10"
76561198027873223,Recommended,293780,20191435,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,Krixtoph,"Amazing 4 player couch co-op game!When I first bought the game things seemed really chaotic and disjointed, but after about 5 minutes in-game things started making a lot of sense: You're basically playing a modified version of playground-style Predator vs Prey. One person starts out as the hero and the other three players (or AI) are ghosts that can inhabit deadly traps to attack the hero, or stand on a pentagram and become a monster with special abilities.The goal of the hero is to level up and beat the dungeon boss, while the goal of the ghosts are to collect ectoplasm to level up, kill the hero, take over his body and kill the boss. Along the way, you stumble upon shops where you can buy trinkets that give you buffs, or new weapons. Going deeper into the dungeon allows all players to level up their summonable monsters which evens the playing field between hero and ghost.The first time I got to play this game with three other friends was when I realized that this game was truly worth the purchase and the risk of buying an early access game. I tend to stay away from EA games unless I see that they have true potential of becoming a complete game, and this one definitely has it. If you're on the fence about getting this game, take my advice and BUY IT! You won't be dissapointed."
