76561197960912290,Recommended,293780,34181367,Posted: 11 August,all,Vividnightmare,"First, this is really only for a group of people to play. This is strictly a multiplayer game. yeah it has single player and the first 2 or 3 times you go through single it is fun, but it gets old really fast. Like a good board game, the real fun comes from familiarity, mastery and competition. When you first start just the design and idea is pretty cool, but as you play and start to learn what everything does and how it works, there comes a depth of planning when playing against friends. The bore comes from the limited set pieces, levels are randomly generated but have a pretty limited amount of props and hazards, so when you play against the computer it very quickly just feels like ""Same old, same old"". With friends you never know what the other players might do, the computer has a pretty standard process of playing the game. The weapons, items, bosses and levels are all kind of randomly rolled out, but from a pretty limited stock. There's only 2 or 3 bosses, a handful of weapons and items and as I said pretty limited level sets. What makes all this fun is human players, randomizing how it is used and doing unexpected things with it. The computer fails to really be inventive, duh, it's a computer. SO, if you have a couple friends that are interested, this will be a blast. However, if you're a hermit like me and rarely have company over or just company that isn't into competitive gaming, you might want to set this one out."
