76561198048981199,Recommended,293780,31673838,Posted: 10 May,all,Slap Factory,Amazing game when it had less than half the content it does now.If you want a game that you and some friends can play on the same screen you have to get this.
,Recommended,293780,30192762,Posted: 26 February,all,Snaith,"Absolutely, without a doubt, one of the best couch multiplayer games I have ever played. In fact, just plain one of the best games I have ever played!The gameplay is fantastic, tight and thrilling. You are one of four adventurers before you turn on one another in a quick and visceral opening scene. Once only one of you is left alive the rest of you take control of your spirits with the options to control monsters, traps and debris in each room as the remaining human player tries to progress. This creates a tense experience as you are always either fighting for your life, just trying to scrape through, or fighting for the chance to regain your humanity - if you kill the human you can restore your humanity and take control of your human body again.As excellent as the core gameplay is, it is the underlying systems that raise the standard to magnificent. The human needs to reach level 10, gaining levels by defeating monsters, then enter the boss room and defeat the boss to win the game. However, every time the player gains a level, making them stronger, the other players gain ""wrath"", a currency they can use to upgrade one of their three possible monsters. Each upgrade tier has two choices, offering a wealth of diversity, and indeed mayhem when all of the effects start flying. With the wrath mechanic those who are not playing as the human get progressively more powerful until they have a good chance of getting the kill and reclaiming their humanity once more.The mechanics of play are simple to understand; one button attacks and another uses your ""special"", a choice of whatever spell that you choose to buy from the blacksmith, gold permitting.  We had two regular gamers and two non regular gamers and everyone was able to compete out fo the gate. Tutorialising is extremely clever in Crawl, other than the buttons you are introduced to each of the ideas of the game through play; for example one of the bosses offers the chance to utilise a healer mid battle so before you enter the boss room he appears and gives you a glimpse of how it works. It is an extremely clever and intuitive process. Similarly, when you enter a new room items that you can interact with flash.The meta game is really quite engaging, too. At the start of each run you choose a deity to worship; this determines the three monsters you are able to use during the run and also a passive bonus. After each run you unlock new deities to worship, new weapons and spells to buy from the blacksmith, new monsters to play as and even new traps to utilise in the dungeons. All of this is to say that as you play more, the options increase and the game becomes even more varied on each play through.In summary, I can't praise Crawl enough. I thoroughly enjoyed every tantalising moment of play, every death throe and every victory. For anyone that enjoys gathering some friends and playing together, both in competition and in co-operation, you can't do any better than Crawl.************************************************************Feedback for the Devs:First, thank you for this amazing game!Second, in my humble opinion, I think a few elements could be tweaked to improve the awesomeness:The monster with the shield special; I think then cooldown is too short when coupled with his impressive speed.Player colours; red and orange can become confused in the heat of play.Loss of control; occassionally it is hard to determine why a player cannot attack (such as when on a pool).Lastly, a few ideas we had...Game modes! Such as on death rotating to the next player in line, rather than on kill. Or a human's health ticks down, ensuring that each turn as the human is finite and the rotation is more likely.Thank you again, for the wonderful Crawl.***************************************************************"
