,Recommended,293780,22856283,"Posted: 7 May, 2016",all,Skypris,"Friends become enemies become friends again in this feverish beat-em-up where you will die the hero, only to see yourself become the villian anyway.This puts a very unique spin on an already established genre, and it does it in a way that makes it stand out against the rest as an example, a goal for how to change game mechanics while maintaining the fun factor.HOW IT PLAYSTo start, it plays like Binding of Isaac or Enter the Gungeon in a sense. Instead of shooting, there is hack n' slash combat. That is where similarities end.When the game start, what happens is a wonderfully crafted, simple yet effective backstory is given as to the 'what and why' of the game. The 4 heroes (up to 4 players or 3 AI) are reduced to 1 while the other players(or AI) now become the spirits. Those spirits are now your enemy.It is the Hero's job to reach at least hero level 10 and kill the boss, all while surviving the traps and monsters that lurk in the dungeon. To do this, the hero will need to stock up on gear and weapons found in the Blcksmiths shop.The spirits are tasked with taking down the hero by means of possesing the traps and summoning runes that lay marked on the floor. Those summoning runes turn the spirits into 1 of 3 monsters from their ""monster loadout"". Once one of them kills the hero, they then take on the role of hero, slayer of ghouls and the fiends they possess.Throughout the game, the hero levels up and sometimes gets rewarded with gold by finding interactive objects or dealing damage to the hero as sppirits. The spirits on the other hand evolve by earning their own currency gained by causing harm to the hero or when the hero levels up.It is a fun and rewarding back and forth game that is surprisingly well balanced with no bugs that I have encountered. I bought this game just a few days before I found it was also part of my Humble Monthly quite some time ago. I did not request a refund from steam for my purchase however because this game is easily worth the money I paid. I would recomend this game to anyone who has local buddies (or can play solo) and loves dungeon crawlers.OTHER THINGS AND STUFFThings it could improve would be to add online functionality, and more diversity to the level design, although neither is required for this already magnificent game.Go give the game a chance!Edit: After spending more time in this game, my review still holds. If anything, I think higher of this game. It is truly something special. They have added more voicework, nee items, a new boss, new mechanics, and new monsters to control. The developers have truly pulled through with this game. Please, go out and play it. It's a hellova good time."
