e, I hurled viscous blades and teeth and flame—To a room most strange and very boss-like.The eldritch stones split a ragged hole in the air, a gateway to the Final Boss above.And winning . . . if you dare take 1 of 3 chances behind.ahem, ahemOkay, now that that’s over with. The results are here:Graphics: Retro, not a bad thing really. It worked well here.Sound: Retro and somewhat repetitive. Like the olden games betwixt the 80s and 90s.Gameplay: Chaotic, but fun. Really fun. Future updates will have to require an indicator to keep track of your player’s location on the screen, though; colors alone are insufficient for something this fast-paced.Replay Value: Oh eff the hell YESSSSSSS!Verdict: A great buy for playing with friends and ganging up on each other. Also hope to play with strangers in multiplayer."
