,Recommended,293780,11591236,"Posted: 7 August, 2014",all,Jungle Rot the Pyronaut,"Well, I saw this game at the bottom of Steam's New Releases list. I'd never seen or heard of the game before, but that pixel art drew me in close enough to click on it. Boy am I glad I did.In Crawl you play as a ghost trying to murder your living friend, or a hero trying to survive your dead friends' onslaught. Hero's can explore the map, break things, buy weapons at the shop, open chests, and attempt to kill the monsters your friends summoned and are controlling. Ghosts can summon monsters when inside a pentagram, possess various kinds of traps throughout the dungeon, spawn slimes if they've collected enough ghost fluff (or whatever it is...), or even take control of a boss the hero is trying to kill.So, the game starts as one of you randomly chosen as the first hero, who goes about the dungeon exploring rooms, and fending off friends who actively try to kill him. ""Why?"" You may ask. Well, the ghost that lands the killing blow on the hero regains their humanity and becomes the new hero, while the dead hero becomes a ghost. And the fight continues.The hero progresses through the dungeon, leveling up by collecting experience from slain monsters. They can buy new weapons, which range from broadswords, to crossbows, to dual throwing knives; special abilities, which allow you to replace your starting dodge roll with better dodging abilities, beserker rage, and lasers; as well as potions and apparel that grant permenant effects like Dragon's Blood that lowers your max health, but makes you deal more damage. My personal favorite, Golem's Blood, which causes you to mave 10% slower, but raises your max health by 40%. Acid cursed rings that causes you to loose pools of acid every time you get hit to damage your attacker, or the shield that floats around you blocking damage altogether. Need some more gold? Cash in all the blood you took from the hero as a ghost to earn a ton of extra cash.Once a hero reaches level 10 they can challenge the boss. The boss is also controlled by the ghosts, who work together to keep the hero from winning the game, because the boss slayer automatically wins first place. If defeated, the hero returns with low life, sure to die within the next few moments.Now, here's the catch. You can only challenge a boss three times before the portal permenently closes. If the hero loses here, not only do they automatically get last place, but they lose that character forever. Normally, even if your the ghosts and lose when someone beats the boss, your character profile is saved, and you can use them again next time. (with all abilities and weapons reset of course) Not if you lose to the boss the third time. If that happens, your gone forever. This allows you to sort of keep a win streak, or stay-alive streak rather. I can't wait to see how the devs use this in the future.Now, heros can level up, so how do the ghosts compensate? They can evolve their monsters. When a hero levels up, each ghost gets Vitae that they can spend evolving monsters when the hero completes a floor. There's lots of monster evolution chains and you can unlock even more. Before you start, each player chooses a deity to worship, which changes the kinds of monsters that are avalible to you as a ghost. Staying the hero for too long will yeild very powerful enemies for you friends, but stay a ghost for too long and you'll never have a shot at beating the game. The longer you stay a ghost, the more powerful your monters become compared to your friends, and the more powerful your monsters, the higher chance you have at landing the killing blow and becomeing the hero. You see? It's all ingeniously ballanced.Yes I can recomend the game right now. Although there's only one boss and and a few deities. The devs are working on more. This is really good for an early access game.On a side note, This game is Lovecraftian as heck. And I love it for that.Only one issue with the game. It's local multiplayer only at this point. Not that I have a big problem with that, but...Now all I need is 3 people willing to sit around a computer screen to play with me :p8/10"
