76561197972366077,Recommended,293780,11970528,"Posted: 3 September, 2014",all,Pab,"Crawl is a quick, frantic, multiplayer frenzy which is awesome to play with friends."
,Recommended,293780,11950062,"Posted: 1 September, 2014",all,Dr. Tran,"Crawl is a a top-tier couch multiplayer game. It has to be one of the best multiplayer games I've ever played. The game mechanics work seamlessly together to create an experience that had me and all of my friends on the edge of our seats with excitement several times over the course of four or five playthroughs. It's rare that we find a game that keeps us so excited for so long.Despite a fairly simple set of mechanics, it manages to keep up the intensity by constantly finding ways to up the ante. The spirit players are consistently evolving their monsters into more powerful forms, but the hero is always gaining more levels and buying loot. Then, when the hero dies the cycle continues for another player. By the time a hero is getting close to level 10 (the required level to fight the boss), the spirits probably have at least one of their monsters at peak evolution--and the peak evolution monsters are almost all bad♥♥♥♥♥hero slaying machines. By that point, every encounter is a desperate scramble to see who can hit level 10 first. The players trade off constantly, each getting their turn to be the hero.Even when someone does hit level 10 and face the boss, the spirits control the boss's various limbs. Good teamwork and coordination can make it incredibly difficult for the hero to succeed; it becomes an intense struggle between the spirits and the hero. Good thing you get 3 chances to beat the boss... but those 3 chances are shared between all players. Some of the most intense moments I've had playing this game came from close calls during the boss fight, but some of the dungeon's rooms can be nearly as treacherous as the boss fight when controlled by good spirit players.The game keeps things fresh by (I think) randomly generating the dungeon's levels every time you play, along with randomizing the loot you can buy from the store. Every time you play, you get new options, and every time you finish a game you unlock new evolutions, traps, or loot. One of the first unlocks is a laser beam trap that we all came to dread greatly when playing as the hero (and love when playing as a spirit). That thing is awesome. You can even unlock new gods to worship (well, only one right now but I imagine they plan on adding more), which open up new monsters and new evolution paths for your monsters.Crawl managed to entertain 7 fickle friends for several hours, even though only four of us at a time could play. It was intense enough and fun enough that it was OK to have to be sidelined, because even watching your friends play is a fairly decent experience. It's hard not to pick sides and start rooting for the spirits or the hero, even if you're not playing. We will *definitely* be playing more of this, especially once more content comes out. The fact that they call this game ""early access"" is incredible. I already feel like I've gotten more than $10 worth of awesome fun out of Crawl, and the fact that more content is coming has me actively excited for more."
