,Recommended,293780,31795438,Posted: 16 May,all,FryeGuy,Crawling in my skin
,Recommended,293780,14569864,"Posted: 20 February, 2015",all,K-Deezy,"This is hands down one of the best local multiplayer games on PC, I don't think my words can really do it justice, in the sense that I'm not all that amazing at writing... but hey? Why not try?So, here's how it goes, you like to have your friends over and play games, you recently purchased an extra controller to play another awesome local multiplayer game, but its quickly becoming boring and you need some variety. (In my case this game was castle crashers.) So, I went on game jolt and saw a banner advertising this game, I decided to buy it.Crawl is a great game in many regards, a fun art style, polished gameplay, surprisingly bug free for an early access game, and constantly changing how you play. A typical round of crawl will go like this, you pick a deity to worship. (This will determine what monsters you get and will give you bonuses as well, ex: shop discounts or extra monster health) And you and you friend(s) spawn in. One of you will be the hero, the others will be the ghosts. The goal of the hero is to kill the other players when they become monsters on pentagrams and get XP to fight a boss when the player reaches level 10. The ghost's goal will be to kill the hero using an assortment of monsters, traps, and cunning. When the ghost kills the hero the ghost takes the hero's place. But, that may be hard as it goes for being a pixelated monster with 3 hit points. So, usually how it goes in my experience is the hero stays the hero for the first dungeon. Anyways at the end of the floor, the monsters will get upgrade points for their monsters depending on how much the hero leveled up. (Monsters also get blood when damaging the player, this will be important later.) So, the next round starts with the ghosts having new, upgraded monsters, and the hero still hasn't gotten enough gold to buy any new items from the shop. The monsters steamroll the player and thus a new hero in born. The new hero can then go to the shop to buy upgrades, weapons, and abilities, by exchanging the blood he/she got for hurting the hero for gold. Crawl Goes like this until one of the heroes has reached level 10, and can challenge one of the two bosses currently in the game, although I'll save those for a surprise, then the round is over. But at the end of each round new weapons, traps, shrines, monsters, and deities are unlocked to keep the gameplay fresh between rounds.So all in all: Do I reccomend crawl?YESThe pixel art, gameplay, monsters, spells, and updates keep the gameplay exciting and every couple of months or so the devs' release a HUGE update with new bosses, evolutions, traps, balances, and weapons. Crawl is by far my favourite local game to play with friends, and this review is coming from a guy who has never even played a dungeon crawler before! Buy Crawl now, you won't be sorry. Trust me"
