76561198081883606,Recommended,293780,18243914,"Posted: 28 September, 2015",all,Ajax,"Can't recomend the game enough. The game is updated every few months providing plenty of time to test out the new additions and get used to the tweaks. The devs are active in the steam forums and are VERY open to discussion and reccomendations.gameplay:one player (chosen at random) controls the hero at the start, the other players are ghosts that control the monsters and traps.dungeons are randomly generated and each room has a minimum pentagram(monster spawn point) equal to the number of players controlling ghosts.each player has 3 monsters based on the god you choose to worship.god can also provide a bonus to your hero character.evolve monsters by damaging or effecting the hero.branching monster evolution tree. While they are fairly limited there is still a large selection and every combination is possible.definitely more fun with people but single player against AI is fun as well.really the only negative is that when playing with 4 people it is possible for one player to be underleveled in one form or the other.if the other 3 players are the only ones getting a chance at being the hero then the 4th player has higher level monsters but the lowest level hero fighting the higher level monsters. granted they will gain xp for killing the hero (which is usually enough for a 1-4 level up). the player would at this point have a massive stockpile of gold (also gained from harming the hero) and can purchase a large amount of upgrades provided they can find the store on that floor.finding the store isnt dificult because the doors are marked with a red stairs (end of floor) blue portal (boss aka how to win the game) an anvil (shop) or a ? if an area is unexplored.ranged weapons have been fixed from earlier versions where they were clunky but are now much smoother to use.bosses: there are 2 bossesa 3 headed hydra where each player controls a headand a squid monster where one player controls the eye and the other 2 control tentacles.great party game"
