,Recommended,293780,11625474,"Posted: 10 August, 2014",all,ShawnMcCool,"Here's a multi-part review discussing how the game works and then information about how my kids of various ages interact with the game.-- How it Works --The game is gorgeous and we all really love how it looks and sounds.Up to 4 players play locally (2 minimum). 1 person plays as a human, the other 3 play as ghosts. The human is seeking gold and experience. Once the human grows up to experience level 10, they make go into a special realm and fight a final end-boss. If they win against the boss, they are the dungeon survivor.The ghosts, on the other hand fly around grabbing orbs. Once they collect enough orbs they're able to drop simple slime monsters into the map. If ANY monster is in a room, then the doors lock and the human must slay them. In some rooms the ghosts may be able to use Monster Symbols to take control of a larger monster and directly fight against the human. In some rooms, the ghosts can possess traps and trigger them against the human. If a ghost kills the human, they come into the game as the human and the dead player returns as a ghost.Here and there you'll find a shop where you can upgrade your spells, weapons, or passive abilities.The entire purpose of the game is to play as a human long enough to get to level 10, then escape the dungeon by killing the boss.What's really fun, is that you only get 1 chance to fight a boss monster per dungeon floor. If you fail, or are not a high enough level, then you most descend further into the dungeon before you can try again. Between each floor in the dungeon, the players can exchange the power they've gained (granted when the human levels up) to evolve their selections of monsters, to effectively increase the difficulty of the next floor of the dungeon.This is definitely a lot of fun.The final boss is a large beast that 3-players can take control of simultaneously against the human. If the players are on point, it's VERY HARD.With only a few players, this game is very very simple. With 4-players actually trying to do a good job, the game is hectic and REALLY shines.-- Family --My 4-year old is a little unsure of the exact goals. But, she does like possessing items in the maps.  But, she gets tired of the game after 1 run-through.The 9-year old has it all figured out and she does a great job.We really like playing this game 4-player as a family. The 4-year old gets a BIT distracted sometimes. But, overall she's ok. I definitely had to take her through the game a few times 2-player with the explicit purpose of showing her around before she could understand it.-- Overall --I can't wait till they add more boss types and dungeon diversity. This game has fantastic style and I trust these developers to make the right decisions for the game."
