76561198027104941,Recommended,293780,30026338,Posted: 18 February,all,luciasar00,"This is the best couch game out of all possible couch games.For context: I play a great deal of couch games with a great variety of people, and what I've learned is that it can be a *challenge* to keep everybody having fun throughout the night. It's one thing to play games with a bunch of Melee pros, or a gaggle of drunk newbies, but what happens when you put them together? Either you play gang beasts, and the tryhards are bored to death, or you put on Samurai Gunn and the poor boy/girlfriend who got roped in gets their♥♥♥♥♥handed to them for the rest of the night. It seems like there's always someone who isn't having fun.But not with Crawl.The terrific basis of Crawl is that losing is *fun*. And the worse you are, the more fun it is. The more the tryhard in your group levels up, the bigger, uglier and more powerful your monsters are. Getting stomped for the first half hour? That's ok, now you have a *giant chicken ogre* to stomp that ****er with. It also serves as an auto-balancing system, so that even the worst player in the group has a chance for an epic comeback.But on the tryhard side, there's a host of options and optimization to sink your teeth into, as well as plenty of things you can pick up to make things more interesting. When one of our guys felt he was rampaging a little too hard, he got the item that gave him massively discounted items in exchange for randomly being turned into a frog - and spent the remainder of the game alternating between a raging fireball of spells and getting pulverized as a helpless amphibian. Taunt the gods to make your victory even sweeter through self-imposed hard-mode. It's a blast.Plus, the art's great. The gameplay is great. The variety and depth of content is great. The replayability is great. The dramatic lovecraft voiceovers at the start of every game are really, really great.There are a lot of good couch games this competes with. Duck game, towerfall, Gang beasts, speed runners... but crawl will always stay at the top of our list. If you've got that hard-to-please varied group of gaming friends who can't ever seem to have fun for a whole evening straight, this is the title for you."
76561198164950785,Recommended,293780,30044583,Posted: 19 February,all,T.C.Firefly,"This game is absolutly amazing! I had the game when it first came out and its only gotten better. It is worth the money, even if you dont have a gorup of friends to play with. The only thing I would want added is more bosses."
,Recommended,293780,30042137,Posted: 19 February,all,Crusher-of-Cities,"Completely surprised by how incredibly fun this is! If you like local multiplayer games, this is pretty much a must!At first glance, this looked like a funny concept that would be amusing for a game or two. Little did I realize how addicting this game can be!Pros:+Very simple controls (only two buttons)+Tons of unlocks and reasons to grind. There's a very large amount of content to unlock through continued gameplay, and what feels like virtually unlimited, Mugen-esque mod potential.+ AI bots - you can play this alone with AI bots tagging in for other players. No need for friends to enjoy it!+ Excellent balance system - Your hero levels up by killing monsters, and your monsters level up by other players' heroes leveling up... meaning in one player is dominating, everyone else gets stronger monsters to try and beat them back down+ Out-of-game challenges - Practice with monsters between games and see what you've unlocked+ Large variety of spells and equipment - Get awesome powers and cool weapons with both magic abilities and even cursed gear+ Cool boss battle concept - Try to win the game with 1vAll boss fightsCons (with suggestions):- The game has the potential to drag - With random gear in the shop, a hero can get powerful quickly or struggle to survive a few rooms in a row. Bosses can be rough without good gear, so there's no easy way to predict if a single playthrough will last 30 minutes or 90. There could probably be some sort of adjustable gold/XP/item-power/wrath settings that would allow players to customize for faster or slower playthroughs.- Only two buttons - Your ghosts have an Inhabit/Attack button, and a Special Attack/Exit button. Many a fight has been thrown at a critical moment by checking for a special attack only to basically forfeit the fight by leaving a monster/object. Just adding a third button for Inhabit/Exit would solve this- No online play - I really, really hope this is something they look into. I would buy a half dozen copies of this in a heartbeat if they added this feature.- Endgame item shopping is often a buyout - As you get to deeper levels, gold accumulates quickly and being the character alive when you enter the item shop usually turns into a shopping spree as you buyout most of the floor. It can be rough to keep your hero alive in endgame without proper gear. The game has a great mechanic of letting a new player teleport to the item shop after reviving his hero AND clearing the room, but that often doesn't help much if you're the second or third person to get to the shop that floor. And if you're undergeared, you probably won't live to the next floor/shop. I should stress, though... while this is an annoyance, it IS NOT game-breakingly bad by any means. This could be fixed with some sort of minimum item system per-player per-floor.Neutral notes:o The game is 1-4 players, and the mood of it changes a lot based on how many there are. 1v1 is a game of slow whittling and constant annoyance. Monster fights are sniping and kiting and trying to break them down over the course of rooms. 4-player games are basically royal rumbles every-other room, and the hero is swarmed with monsters, dies, is replaced by another player's hero who now still has to deal with the leftovers. Control often changes hands twice in a single room. 3-players is my favorite balance so far. Some sort of optional monster handicap setting could add more variety (option to boost in 1v1 for easier turnover, option to weaken in 4-player to make surviving longer easier)"
