76561197972862521,Recommended,293780,27327393,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,]Eggs[SharpShooter,"Crawl has become, unexpectedly, one of my favorite games. As an indie game, it will be money well spent (privded you have people to play with for some fantastic couch co-op). Get it, its great.I own a lot of shared/split-screen games. I tend to organize a bunch of team sports, and pre-drinking is mandatory. To this end, having simple to play, local co-op games is a must for some good rowdy entertainemt. Crawl is simple to play (moderately hard to master). There are only two buttons, attack and special but the hook is that it is dynamic 3v1 set up. A 'human' player competes against three 'ghosts' to gain enough levels to be the one that challenges the boss. Ghosts inhabit monsters to kill the 'human'. The one that lands the deadly blow becomes 'human'. As 'human' players level, ghosts get currency to in turn level up their mosters. Thus, if you can't get a kill on a human and everyone levels around you, you will have more to spen on leveling monsters, ergo a higher chance of getting the kill. As monsters do damage to humans they gain currency they can use if they become human in a shop to increase their effectiveness. Once someone reaches enough power to challenge a boss, the 3 ghots comibine to controll that boss to fight. Overall, the game design is solid, unique, and super fun. If there are no monsters to inhabit, ghost characters can controll various traps and jump into items to harrass the 'human'.I've had this game for a long time and the developers are still providing updates with more monster evolutions, more items to purchas in the shop, and more trap dynamics. The only even remotely (possibly)negative thing is they have yet to add to the roster of end game bosses (currently there are only 2).While the overall this is a simple game there is a slight learning curve (mainly what are the monster attack/specials, possible human specials). There is progression (unlocking monster evolves/items), but it is pretty quick. Super casual players may be turned off by this, but overall, whenever I bust this game out, response is always positive."
76561198019244812,Recommended,293780,31976107,Posted: 26 May,all,TranceAddict82,If you have friends to play this with locally its a blast.
76561198200064499,Recommended,293780,32000592,Posted: 27 May,all,Dr3amSoda,"Crawl is an amazing game that took a unique concept and expanded it into something huge allowing the player(s) to play as both the hero and the villain. The game has a pretty balanced battle system that allows both sides of gameplay to feel like they're on the same level. The game has a cool collection of monsters with its own set of attacks as well as designs that really make the game stand out, the game also allows the human to play very differently with stat decreases and increases and different weapon types that each have different effects. While I do believe that this is a fantastic game, I feel like its missing quite a lot of aspects that would make it a masterpiece. Firstly, while the game is quite fun as a local game, this game is missing out because of its exclusion of a multiplayer online feature. Another thing I believe that the game should have is more bosses. The game uses the same three bosses and after fightingKourokfor the 20th time it starts to get a little repetitive, the addition of more bosses and monsters would drastically spice up the gameplay. All in all, I believe Crawl is a pretty good game and while I do hope they add online- multiplayer, I still recommend this to those that want to play a fun dungeon crawler with friends close by."
